<text id="02-output-contract" title="QA Prioritization Rubric — Output Contract" version="1.0.0" est_tokens="700" depth="essential">
  <summary>A scoring artefact: 4–7 named dimensions, each with 1–5 BARS anchors, an explicit aggregation rule, and per-score evidence pointers.</summary>

  <section title="Required fields">
    <list>
      <item>dimension.name + dimension.anchors (5 anchor descriptions)</item>
      <item>score.value (1–5) + score.evidence (verbatim pointer)</item>
      <item>aggregation_rule (min | weighted_sum | veto_on_1)</item>
      <item>calibration.last_run_at + calibration.reviewers (≥ 2)</item>
      <item>version + owner + last_calibrated_at</item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <section title="Forbidden patterns">
    <antipattern>
      <description>dimension &apos;subjective overall&apos; or similar</description>
      <reason>Unanchored dimensions collapse the score.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>score without evidence pointer</description>
      <reason>Opinion-scoring with no defence.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>aggregation by &apos;reviewer feeling&apos;</description>
      <reason>Hides poor dimensions; not reproducible.</reason>
    </antipattern>
    <antipattern>
      <description>calibration &gt; 6 months stale</description>
      <reason>Anchors drift from current reality.</reason>
    </antipattern>
  </section>

  <section title="Self-check checklist">
    <list>
      <item>4–7 dimensions with 5-point anchored scales.</item>
      <item>Each score carries verbatim evidence.</item>
      <item>Aggregation rule is published and applied.</item>
      <item>Calibration pass run in the last 6 months.</item>
      <item>Versioned + named owner.</item>
    </list>
  </section>
</text>
